                     \u003Cregion>Sicily\u003C/region>\n                        \u003Csettlement>Segesta\u003C/settlement>\n                        \u003Crepository role=\"site\" ref=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/196\">Parco archeologico di Segesta\u003C/repository>\n                        \u003Cidno type=\"inventory\">SG 7578 + 7579 + 7580 + 7581 + 10782 (uninscribed)\u003C/idno>\n                        \u003C!--No inventory number found-->\n                        \u003C!--Adding location for old id numbers if available-->\n                        \u003CaltIdentifier>\n                            \u003Csettlement/>\n                            \u003Crepository/>\n                            \u003Cidno type=\"old\"/>\n                        \u003C/altIdentifier>\n                    \u003C/msIdentifier>\n                    \u003CmsContents>\n                        \u003CtextLang mainLang=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/textLang>\n                    \u003C/msContents>\n                    \u003CphysDesc>\n                        \u003CobjectDesc>\n                            \u003CsupportDesc>\n                                \u003Csupport>\u003Cp>Five slabs from the pavement of the bouleuterion, confirmed to come from the area of the entrance of the portico, of which the first (to the left) is uninscribed, the other four bearing four lines of Greek letters. The individual slabs are 74 cm in width.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.stone\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/2.html\">stone\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.pavement\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/190.html\">pavement\u003C/objectType>\n                                    \u003Cdimensions>\u003C!--ISegesta-->\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">75.5\u003C/height>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\">387.6\u003C/width>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\">14-38.5\u003C/depth>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Large, thinly carved letters of wide module. Alpha with broken bar; epsilon with equal width horizontal strokes; kappa with short arms; theta and omicron full size; theta with detached cross-bar; pi with overlapping cross-bar; sigma with horizontal outer strokes, shallow inner strokes; omicron rhomboid and closed.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line4\">Line 1-4\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"84\" atMost=\"98\">84-98\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"https://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462487\">Segesta\u003C/placeName>\t\t\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2523171\">Segesta\u003C/placeName>\n                            \t\u003Cgeo>37.94171, 12.83649\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"-0130\" notAfter-custom=\"-0101\" evidence=\"archaeological-context lettering\">end of the second century BCE on archaeological grounds.\u003C/origDate>\n                        \u003C/origin>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\">The second slab from the left first observed by Gualtherus in the ruins of the site; the other four slabs were found in excavation in 1997 of the collapse of a room of mediaeval date constructed on top of the bouletuerion, except for the first, uninscribed slab, which was in re-use in a near-by cistern.\u003Cgeo>37.9398101,12.8414193\u003C/geo>\u003C/provenance>\u003C!-- location of bouleterion -->\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\">None\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cacquisition/>\n                    \u003C/history>\n                    \u003C/msDesc>\n            \u003C/sourceDesc>\n        \u003C/fileDesc>\n        \u003CencodingDesc>\n             \u003Cp>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines\u003C/p>\n             \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 \u003Cxi:fallback>\n                     \u003Cp>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values\u003C/p>\n                 \u003C/xi:fallback>\n             \u003C/xi:include>\n\t  \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     \u003Cxi:fallback>\n\t       \u003Cp>ISicily glyphs authority list\u003C/p>\n\t     \u003C/xi:fallback>\n\t   \u003C/xi:include>\n         \u003C/encodingDesc>\n        \u003CprofileDesc>\n            \u003CcalendarDesc>\n                \u003Ccalendar xml:id=\"julian\">\n                    \u003Cp>Julian Calendar\u003C/p>\n                \u003C/calendar>\n            \u003C/calendarDesc>\n            \u003ClangUsage>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"en\">English\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"it\">Italian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"la\">Latin\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"he\">Hebrew\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"phn\">Phoenician\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xpu\">Punic\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"osc\">Oscan\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xly\">Elymian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"scx\">Sikel\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"sxc\">Sikan\u003C/language>\n            \u003C/langUsage>\n            \u003CtextClass>\n                \u003Ckeywords scheme=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins.html\">\n                    \u003Cterm ana=\"#function.building\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/86.html\">building\u003C/term>\n                \u003C/keywords>\n            \u003C/textClass>\n        \u003C/profileDesc>\n        \u003CrevisionDesc status=\"draft\">\n            \u003ClistChange>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2016-12-03\" who=\"#JCu\">James Cummings autogenerated EpiDoc output from database\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2019-09-23\" who=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag added ISegesta ref\u003C/change>\n            \t   \u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-05\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova normalised Unicode\u003C/change>\n            \t   \u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-08\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova updated list of languages\u003C/change>\n            \t\u003Cchange when=\"2020-11-20\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova added EDCS numbers\u003C/change>\n\t\t\u003Cchange when=\"2020-11-26\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova restructured bibliography\u003C/change>\n\t    \u003Cchange when=\"2020-12-23\" who=\"#JP\">Updated Zenodo DOI\u003C/change>\n            \t\u003Cchange when=\"2021-01-19\" who=\"#SS\">renumbered files, uris and references\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2021-07-12\" who=\"#AL\">Andoni Llamazares added text edition\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2026-03-04\" who=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag revised metadata from publication\u003C/change>\n\t\u003C/listChange>\n        \u003C/revisionDesc>\n    \u003C/teiHeader>\n    \u003Cfacsimile>\u003Csurface/>\u003C!-- \n        \u003Csurface type=\"front\">\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic003505_tiled.tif\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic003505.jpg\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n         \u003C/surface> -->\n    \u003C/facsimile>\n    \u003Ctext>\n        \u003Cbody>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"edition\" subtype=\"primary\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"grc\" resp=\"#AL\" source=\"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/3PK3JKXR\">\n                \u003Cab>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"1\"/>\u003CpersName type=\"attested\">\u003Cname>Ἄσκλαπος\u003C/name> \u003CpersName type=\"attested\">\u003Cname type=\"patronym\">Διοδώρου\u003C/name>\u003C/persName> \u003Cname type=\"secondName\">Ταυρέας\u003C/name>\u003C/persName>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"2\"/>\u003CroleName type=\"civic\" subtype=\"epistates\">\u003Cw>ἐπιστάτας\u003C/w>\u003C/roleName>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"3\"/>\u003CpersName type=\"attested\">\u003Cname>Βίβακος\u003C/name> \u003CpersName type=\"attested\">\u003Cname type=\"patronym\">Τιττέλου\u003C/name>\u003C/persName> \u003Cname type=\"secondName\">Ποσθαῖος\u003C/name>\u003C/persName>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"4\"/>\u003Cw>ἀρχιτεκτόνησε\u003C/w>\n                \u003C/ab>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"apparatus\">\n                \u003ClistApp>\n                    \u003Capp>\u003Cnote>text according to Ampolo and Erdas 2019\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                \u003C/listApp>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"en\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cp>Asklapos Taureas, son of Diodorus, was the overseer. Bibakos Posthaios, son of Tittelos, was the architect.\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"commentary\">\n                \u003Cp>\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"bibliography\">\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    \u003Cbibl type=\"corpus\" n=\"IG\">\n                        \u003Cauthor>Kaibel\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1890\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>\n                            \u003Cref target=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\">292\u003C/ref>\n                        \u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/Q2SBPG9F\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl type=\"bulletin\" n=\"SEG\">\n                        \u003CcitedRange>50.1020\u003C/citedRange>\n               